# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Git Commit Agent — Environment Variables
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Copy this file and configure the values in your Lamatic Studio environment.
# Do NOT commit a filled-in version of this file — .env and .env.local are
# already in .gitignore.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# ── GitHub (optional for public repos) ───────────────────────────────────────

# Personal Access Token (classic) or Fine-grained token with read:repo scope.
# Required for:  private repositories
# Recommended for: avoiding the 60 req/hr unauthenticated rate limit
# How to get:    https://github.com/settings/tokens → "Generate new token"
# Minimum scope: public_repo (public repos), repo (private repos)
GITHUB_TOKEN=

# ── LLM Provider ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Configure your LLM provider API key directly in Lamatic Studio:
#   Studio → Your Project → Flow → LLM Node → Provider & API Key
#
# Common provider keys (set whichever you use in Studio):
OPENAI_API_KEY=
ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=
GROQ_API_KEY=
